Sentinel-2 with eo-learn¶

This exercise explores the eo-learn library capacities downloading and saving Sentinel-2 imaging data.

In [1]:
from eolearn.io import S2L1CWCSInput, AddSen2CorClassificationFeature, DEMWCSInput, S2L2AWCSInput, L8L1CWCSInput
from eolearn.core import SaveTask, LoadTask
from eolearn.core.eoworkflow import LinearWorkflow, Dependency
from eolearn.core.eodata import FeatureType
%matplotlib inline
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import datetime
from sentinelhub import BBox, CRS #registration and configuration required

#sentinelhub registration: https://sentinelhub-py.readthedocs.io/en/latest/examples/ogc_request.html
#sentinelhub configuration: https://sentinelhub-py.readthedocs.io/en/latest/configure.html

Define bounding box and time interval for EO images:

In [2]:
roi_bbox = BBox(bbox=[4.50, 43.33, 4.90, 43.50], crs=CRS.WGS84) #lon_min, lat_max, lon_max, lat_min; max size = 5000x5000
time_interval = ('2019-06-01', '2019-07-01')

Specify the layers you want to include for visualization. In this case: S2 L1C and L2A, NDVI and a scene classification (SCL).

In [3]:
input_task = S2L1CWCSInput(layer = 'BANDS-S2-L1C', resx = '20m', resy = '20m',
                           maxcc = .8, time_difference = datetime.timedelta(hours = 2))

add_ndvi = S2L1CWCSInput(layer = 'NDVI')

add_l2a = S2L2AWCSInput(layer = 'BANDS-S2-L2A')

add_sen2cor = AddSen2CorClassificationFeature('SCL', layer = 'BANDS-S2-L2A')

save = SaveTask('S2_eolearn_data', overwrite_permission = 2, compress_level = 1) 

# the folder "S2_eolearn_data" is created within the code's path, if no path is specified.

Run workflow and save the data requested. The bigger is the area selected, the slower is this part.

In [4]:
workflow = LinearWorkflow(input_task, add_ndvi, add_l2a, add_sen2cor, save)

result = workflow.execute({input_task: {'bbox': roi_bbox, 'time_interval': time_interval},
                           save: {'eopatch_folder': 'eopatch'}})

eopatch = result[save]

1 - SC_SATURATED_DEFECTIVE, 2 - SC_DARK_FEATURE_SHADOW , 3 - SC_CLOUD_SHADOW, 4 - VEGETATION, 5 - NOT-VEGETATED, 6 - WATER, 7 - SC_CLOUD_LOW_PROBA / UNCLASSIFIED, 8 - SC_CLOUD_MEDIUM_PROBA, 9 - CLOUD_HIGH_PROBABILITY, 10 - THIN_CIRRUS, 11 - SNOW
